race.comment: BOTTAS (4) wasted no time getting off the mark as favourite on debut over 1710m at Saratoga (Turf) six weeks ago. Has plenty of upside and can win again. NOBLE DYNASTY (8) landed his maiden success over this course and distance last time, scoring by 0.1 lengths. Is lightly raced and has plenty of scope for improvement. Shaping up nicely and he is worth including. SCOPE (6) did a fair job on debut last time out, finishing one length from the winner in second over 1710m at Saratoga (Turf). One of the main contenders. REPENTLESS (10) won on debut last time out four weeks ago over 1408m at Kentucky, getting home by 3 lengths. Can give this a shake.
